"title": "4478: meat",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4478: meat",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The flesh of animals, consumed as food. In biblical times it was a luxury, eaten on special occasions, usually in the context of sacrificial worship.</p>\n<h2>Meat a luxury food</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:3\">EXO 16:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:4-Num11:5\">NUM 11:4–11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:11\">1SA 25:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:12-Isa22:13\">ISA 22:12–22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:3\">DAN 10:3</a></p>\n<h2>Meat served to honoured guests</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:21-1Sam28:25\">1SA 28:21–28:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:1-Gen18:8\">GEN 18:1–18:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:11-Judg6:21\">JDG 6:11–6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:9-Judg13:16\">JDG 13:9–13:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:22-1Sam9:24\">1SA 9:22–9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:1-2Sam12:4\">2SA 12:1–12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:19-1Kgs19:21\">1KI 19:19–19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:1-Prov9:6\">PRO 9:1–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:6\">ISA 25:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:20-Luke15:24\">LUK 15:20–15:24</a></p>\n<h2>Meat provided by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:2-1Kgs17:6\">1KI 17:2–17:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:1-Exod16:14\">EXO 16:1–16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:4-Num11:34\">NUM 11:4–11:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:17-Ps78:31\">PSA 78:17–78:31</a></p>\n<h2>Restrictions on eating certain types of meat</h2>\n<h3>Unclean meat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:1-Lev11:47\">LEV 11:1–11:47</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:3-Deut14:20\">DEU 14:3–14:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:2-Isa65:5\">ISA 65:2–65:5</a></p>\n<h3>Other prohibited meat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:4\">GEN 9:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:28\">EXO 21:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:31\">EXO 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:26\">LEV 19:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:23\">DEU 12:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:21\">DEU 14:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:33-1Sam14:34\">1SA 14:33–14:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:14\">EZK 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:25\">EZK 33:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:20\">ACT 15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:29\">ACT 15:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:25\">ACT 21:25</a></p>\n<h2>Eating meat in worship</h2>\n<h3>The Passover lamb</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:1-Exod12:11\">EXO 12:1–12:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:43-Exod12:49\">EXO 12:43–12:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:1-Deut16:8\">DEU 16:1–16:8</a></p>\n<h3>Other sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:31-Exod29:34\">EXO 29:31–29:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:11-Lev7:18\">LEV 7:11–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:14-Num18:19\">NUM 18:14–18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:27\">DEU 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:3-1Sam1:8\">1SA 1:3–1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:12-1Sam2:16\">1SA 2:12–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:21\">JER 7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:13\">HOS 8:13</a></p>\n<h2>Non-consecrated meat</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:4-Deut12:25\">DEU 12:4–12:25</a></p>\n<h2>Allegorical and metaphorical references to meat</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:1-Mic3:3\">MIC 3:1–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:1-Ezek11:12\">EZK 11:1–11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:1-Ezek24:13\">EZK 24:1–24:13</a></p>\n<h2>Varying convictions about eating meat</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1-Rom14:23\">ROM 14:1–14:23</a></p>",
